INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.149','Beta-primeverosidase','NULL','NULL','The enzyme is responsible for the formation of the alcoholic aroma inoolong and black tea.In addition to beta-primeverosides (i.e. 6-O-(beta-D-xylopyranosyl)-beta-D-glucopyranosides), it also hydrolyzes 6-O-(beta-D-apiofuranosyl)-beta-D-glucopyranosides and, less rapidly, beta-vicianosides and 6-O-(alpha-L-arabinofuranosyl)-beta-D-glucopyranosides, but not beta-glucosides.Geranyl-, linaloyl-, benzyl- and p-nitrophenol glycosides are allhydrolyzed.','A 6-O-(beta-D-xylopyranosyl)-beta-D-glucopyranoside + H(2)O = 6-O-(beta-D-xylopyranosyl)-beta-D-glucopyranose + an alcohol.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.150','Oligoxyloglucan reducing-end-specific cellobiohydrolase','NULL','NULL','The enzyme is found in the fungus Geotrichum sp. M128.The substrate is a hemicellulose found in plant cell walls.','Hydrolysis of cellobiose from the reducing end of xyloglucans consistingof a beta-(1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.151','Xyloglucan-specific endo-beta-1,4-glucanase','1,4-beta-D-glucan glucanohydrolase','NULL','The enzyme from Aspergillus aculeatus is specific for xyloglucan anddoes not hydrolyze other cell-wall components.The reaction involves endohydrolysis of 1,4-beta-D-glucosidiclinkages in xyloglucan with retention of the beta-configuration ofthe glycosyl residues.','Xyloglucan + H(2)O = xyloglucan oligosaccharides.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.152','Mannosylglycoprotein endo-beta-mannosidase','Endo-beta-mannosidase','NULL','The substrate group is a substituent on N-4 of an asparagine residuein the glycoprotein.The mannose residue at the non-reducing end of the sequence may carryfurther alpha-D-mannosyl groups on O-3 or O-6, but such a substituenton O-3 of the beta-D-mannosyl group prevents the action of theenzyme.The enzyme was obtained from the lily, Lilium longiflorum.','Hydrolysis of the alpha-D-mannosyl-(1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.153','Fructan beta-(2,1)-fructosidase','1-FEH II','NULL','Possesses one of the activities of EC 3.2.1.80.While the best substrates are the inulin-type fructans, such as1-kestose (beta-D-fructofuranosyl-(2-','Hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing (2-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.154','Fructan beta-(2,6)-fructosidase','6-FEH','NULL','Possesses one of the activities of EC 3.2.1.80.While the best substrates are the levan-type fructans such as6-kestotriose (beta-D-fructofuranosyl-(2-','Hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing (2-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.155','Xyloglucan-specific exo-beta-1,4-glucanase','NULL','NULL','The enzyme removes XXXG heptasaccharides, XXLG/XLXG octasaccharidesand XLLG nonasaccharides from the end of tamarind seed xyloglucanpolymers in a processive manner.Hydrolysis occurs at the unsubstituted D-glucopyranose residue in themain backbone.It is not known whether the cleavage takes place at the reducing ornon-reducing end of the polymer.Very low activity with beta-D-glucans.The enzyme from Chrysosporium lucknowense shifts to an endoglucanasemode when acting on linear substrates without bulky substituents onthe polymeric backbone such as barley beta-glucan.Formerly EC 3.2.1.160.','Hydrolysis of (1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.156','Oligosaccharide reducing-end xylanase','Reducing end xylose-releasing exo-oligoxylanase','NULL','The enzyme, originally isolated from the bacterium Bacillushalodurans C-125, releases the xylose unit at the reducing end ofoligosaccharides ending with the structure beta-D-xylopyranosyl-(1-','Hydrolysis of (1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.157','Iota-carrageenase','NULL','NULL','The main products of hydrolysis are iota-neocarratetraose sulfate andiota-neocarrahexaose sulfate.Iota-neocarraoctaose is the shortest substrate oligomer that can becleaved.Unlike EC 3.2.1.81 and EC 3.2.1.83, this enzyme proceeds withinversion of the anomeric configuration.Iota-carrageenan differs from kappa-carrageenan by possessing a sulfogroup on O-2 of the 3,6-anhydro-D-galactose residues, in addition tothat present in the kappa-compound on O-4 of the D-galactoseresidues.','Endohydrolysis of 1,4-beta-D-linkages between D-galactose 4-sulfate and3,6-anhydro-D-galactose-2-sulfate in iota-carrageenans.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.158','Alpha-agarase','Agarase A33','Calcium.','The enzyme from Thalassomonas sp. can use agarose, agarohexaose andneoagarohexaose as substrate.The products of agarohexaose hydrolysis are dimers and tetramers,with agarotetraose being the predominant product, whereas hydrolysisof neoagarohexaose gives rise to two types of trimer.While the enzyme can also hydrolyze the highly sulfated agaroseporphyran very efficiently, it cannot hydrolyze kappa-carrageenan andiota-carrageenan.','Endohydrolysis of 1,3-alpha-L-galactosidic linkages in agarose, yieldingagarotetraose as the major product.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.159','Alpha-neoagaro-oligosaccharide hydrolase','Alpha-NAOS hydrolase','NULL','When neoagarohexaose is used as a substrate, the oligosaccharide iscleaved at the non-reducing end to produce 3,6-anhydro-L-galactoseand agaropentaose, which is further hydrolyzed to agarobiose andagarotriose.With neoagarotetraose as substrate, the products are predominantlyagarotriose and 3,6-anhydro-L-galactose.In Vibrio sp. the actions of EC 3.2.1.81 and EC 3.2.1.159 can be usedto degrade agarose to 3,6-anhydro-L-galactose and D-galactose.','Hydrolysis of the 1,3-alpha-L-galactosidic linkages of neoagaro-oligosaccharides that are smaller than a hexamer, yielding 3,6-anhydro-L-galactose and D-galactose.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.160','Transferred entry: 3','NULL','NULL','NULL','NULL', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.161','Beta-apiosyl-beta-glucosidase','Furcatin hydrolase','NULL','Removes disaccharides from the natural substrates dalpatein 7-O-beta-D-apiofuranosyl-(1-','7-(beta-D-apiofuranosyl-(1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.162','Lambda-carrageenase','Endo-beta-1,4-carrageenose 2,6,2-trisulfate-hydrolase','NULL','The enzyme from Pseudoalteromonas sp. is specific for lambda-carrageenan.Iota-carrageenan (see EC 3.2.1.157), kappa-carrageenan (seeEC 3.2.1.83), agarose and porphyran are not substrates.','Endohydrolysis of (1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.163','1,6-alpha-D-mannosidase','NULL','NULL','Specific for (1-','Hydrolysis of the 1,6-linked alpha-D-mannose residues in alpha-D-Manp-(1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.164','Galactan endo-1,6-beta-galactosidase','Endo-1,6-beta-galactanase','NULL','Specifically hydrolyzes 1,6-beta-D-galactooligosaccharides with adegree of polymerization (DP) higher than 3, and their acidicderivatives with 4-O-methylglucosyluronate or glucosyluronate groupsat the non-reducing terminals.1,3-beta-D- and 1,4-beta-D-galactosyl residues cannot act assubstrates.Can also hydrolyze alpha-L-arabinofuranosidase-treatedarabinogalactan protein (AGP) extracted from radish roots.AGPs are thought to be involved in many physiological events, such ascell division, cell expansion and cell death.','Endohydrolysis of (1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.165','Exo-1,4-beta-D-glucosaminidase','Exo-beta-D-glucosaminidase','NULL','Chitosan is a partially or totally N-deacetylated chitin derivativethat is found in the cell walls of some phytopathogenic fungi andcomprises D-glucosamine residues with a variable content of GlcNAcresidues.Acts specifically on chitooligosaccharides and chitosan, havingmaximal activity on chitotetraose, chitopentaose and theircorresponding alcohols.Can degrade GlcN-GlcNAc but not GlcNAc-GlcNAc.','Hydrolysis of chitosan or chitosan oligosaccharides to remove successiveD-glucosamine residues from the non-reducing termini.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.166','Heparanase','Hpa1 heparanase','NULL','Heparanase cleaves the linkage between a glucuronic acid unit and anN-sulfo glucosamine unit carrying either a 3-O-sulfo or a 6-O-sulfogroup.Heparanase-1 cuts macromolecular heparin into fragments of 5000-20000Da.The enzyme cleaves the heparan sulfate glycosaminoglycans fromproteoglycan core proteins and degrades them to smalloligosaccharides.Inside cells, the enzyme is important for the normal catabolism ofheparan sulfate proteoglycans, generating glycosaminoglycan fragmentsthat are then transported to lysosomes and completely degraded.When secreted, heparanase degrades basement membrane heparan sulfateglycosaminoglycans at sites of injury or inflammation, allowingextravasion of immune cells into nonvascular spaces and releasingfactors that regulate cell proliferation and angiogenesis.','Endohydrolysis of (1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.167','Baicalin-beta-D-glucuronidase','Baicalinase','NULL','The enzyme also hydrolyzes wogonin 7-O-beta-D-glucuronide andoroxylin 7-O-beta-D-glucuronide with lower efficiency.Neglegible activity with p-nitrophenyl-beta-D-glucuronide.','Baicalin + H(2)O = baicalein + D-glucuronate.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.168','Hesperidin 6-O-alpha-L-rhamnosyl-beta-D-glucosidase','NULL','NULL','The enzyme exhibits high specificity toward 7-O-linked flavonoidbeta-rutinosides.','Hesperidin + H(2)O = hesperetin + rutinose.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.169','Protein O-GlcNAcase','Glycoside hydrolase O-GlcNAcase','NULL','Within higher eukaryotes post-translational modification of proteinserines/threonines with N-acetylglucosamine (O-GlcNAc) is dynamic,inducible and abundant, regulating many cellular processes byinterfering with protein phosphorylation.EC 2.4.1.155 transfers GlcNAc onto substrate proteins andEC 3.2.1.169 cleaves GlcNAc from the modified proteins.','(1) [Protein]-3-O-(N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl)-L-serine + H(2)O = [protein]-L-serine + N-acetyl-D-glucosamine.(2) [Protein]-3-O-(N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl)-L-threonine + H(2)O =[protein]-L-threonine + N-acetyl-D-glucosamine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.170','Mannosylglycerate hydrolase','2-O-(6-phospho-mannosyl)-D-glycerate hydrolase','NULL','The enzyme participates in the mannosylglycerate degradation pathwayof some bacteria.Mannosylglycerate is phosphorylated during transport into the cell,and the phosphorylated form is hydrolyzed by this enzyme.','2-O-(6-phospho-alpha-D-mannosyl)-D-glycerate + H(2)O = D-mannose6-phosphate + D-glycerate.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.171','Rhamnogalacturonan hydrolase','RG-hydrolase','NULL','The enzyme is part of the degradation system for rhamnogalacturonan Iin Aspergillus aculeatus.','Endohydrolysis of alpha-D-GalA-(1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.172','Unsaturated rhamnogalacturonyl hydrolase','NULL','NULL','The enzyme is part of the degradation system for rhamnogalacturonan Iin Bacillus subtilis strain 168.','2-O-(4-deoxy-beta-L-threo-hex-4-enopyranuronosyl)-alpha-L-rhamnopyranose+ H(2)O = 5-dehydro-4-deoxy-D-glucuronate + L-rhamnopyranose.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.173','Rhamnogalacturonan galacturonohydrolase','RG-galacturonohydrolase','NULL','The enzyme is part of the degradation system for rhamnogalacturonan Iin Aspergillus aculeatus.','Exohydrolysis of the alpha-D-GalA-(1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.174','Rhamnogalacturonan rhamnohydrolase','RG alpha-L-rhamnopyranohydrolase','NULL','The enzyme is part of the degradation system for rhamnogalacturonan Iin Aspergillus aculeatus.','Exohydrolysis of the alpha-L-Rha-(1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.175','Beta-D-glucopyranosyl abscisate beta-glucosidase','ABA-beta-D-glucosidase','NULL','The enzyme hydrolzes the biologically inactive beta-D-glucopyranosylester of abscisic acid to produce active abscisate.Abscisate is a phytohormone critical for plant growth, developmentand adaption to various stress conditions.The enzyme does not hydrolyze beta-D-glucopyranosyl zeatin.','D-glucopyranosyl abscisate + H(2)O = D-glucose + abscisate.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.176','Cellulose 1,4-beta-cellobiosidase (reducing end)','Cellulase SS','NULL','Some exocellulases, most of which belong to the glycoside hydrolasefamily 48 (GH48), act at the reducing ends of cellulose and similarsubstrates.The CelS enzyme from Clostridium thermocellum is the most abundantsubunit of the cellulosome formed by the organism.It liberates cellobiose units from the reducing end by hydrolysis ofthe glycosidic bond, employing an inverting reaction mechanism.Different from EC 3.2.1.91, which attacks cellulose from the non-reducing end.','Hydrolysis of (1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.177','Alpha-D-xyloside xylohydrolase','Alpha-xylosidase','NULL','The enzyme catalyzes hydrolysis of a terminal, unsubstituted xylosideat the extreme reducing end of a xylogluco-oligosaccharide.Representative alpha-xylosidases from glycoside hydrolase family 31utilize a two-step (double-displacement) mechanism involving acovalent glycosyl-enzyme intermediate, and retain the anomericconfiguration of the product.','Hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing alpha-D-xylose residues with releaseof alpha-D-xylose.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.178','Beta-porphyranase','Endo-beta-porphyranase','NULL','The backbone of porphyran consists largely (approximately 70%) of(1-','Hydrolysis of beta-D-galactopyranose-(1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.179','Gellan tetrasaccharide unsaturated glucuronyl hydrolase','Unsaturated glucuronyl hydrolase','NULL','The enzyme releases 4-deoxy-4(5)-unsaturated D-glucuronic acid fromoligosaccharides produced by polysaccharide lyases, e.g. thetetrasaccharide beta-D-4-deoxy-Delta(4)-GlcAp-(1-','Beta-D-4-deoxy-Delta(4)-GlcAp-(1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.180','Unsaturated chondroitin disaccharide hydrolase','Unsaturated glucuronyl hydrolase','NULL','The enzyme releases 4-deoxy-4,5-didehydro D-glucuronic acid or4-deoxy-4,5-didehydro L-iduronic acid from chondroitin disaccharides,hyaluronan disaccharides and heparin disaccharides and cleaves bothglycosidic (1-','Beta-D-4-deoxy-Delta(4)-GlcAp-(1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.181','Galactan endo-beta-1,3-galactanase','Endo-beta-1,3-galactanase','NULL','The enzyme from the fungus Flammulina velutipes (winter mushroom)hydrolyzes the beta(1-','The enzyme specifically hydrolyzes beta-1,3-galactan and beta-1,3-galactooligosaccharides.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.182','4-hydroxy-7-methoxy-3-oxo-3,4-dihydro-2H-1,4-benzoxazin-2-yl glucosidebeta-D-glucosidase','DIMBOA glucosidase','NULL','The enzyme from Triticum aestivum (wheat) has a higher affinity forDIMBOA glucoside than DIBOA glucoside.With Secale cereale (rye) the preference is reversed.','(1) (2R)-4-hydroxy-7-methoxy-3-oxo-3,4-dihydro-2H-1,4-benzoxazin-2-ylbeta-D-glucopyranoside + H(2)O = 2,4-dihydroxy-7-methoxy-2H-1,4-benzoxazin-3(4H)-one + D-glucose.(2) (2R)-4-hydroxy-3-oxo-3,4-dihydro-2H-1,4-benzoxazin-2-yl beta-D-glucopyranoside + H(2)O = 2,4-dihydroxy-2H-1,4-benzoxazin-3(4H)-one +D-glucose.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.183','UDP-N-acetylglucosamine 2-epimerase (hydrolyzing)','UDP-N-acetylglucosamine 2-epimerase','NULL','The enzyme is found in mammalian liver, as well as in some pathogenicbacteria including Neisseria meningitidis and Staphylococcus aureus.It catalyzes the first step of sialic acid (N-acetylneuraminic acid)biosynthesis.The initial product formed is the alpha anomer, which rapidlymutarotates to a mixture of anomers.The mammalian enzyme is bifunctional and also catalyzes EC 2.7.1.60.Cf. EC 5.1.3.14.','UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine + H(2)O = N-acetyl-D-mannosamine + UDP.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.184','UDP-N,N-diacetylbacillosamine 2-epimerase (hydrolyzing)','UDP-Bac2Ac(4)Ac 2-epimerase','Magnesium.','Involved in biosynthesis of legionaminic acid, a nonulosonatederivative that is incorporated by some bacteria into assortedvirulence-associated cell surface glycoconjugates.The initial product formed by the enzyme from Legionella pneumophila,which incorporates legionaminic acid into the O-antigen moiety of itslipopolysaccharide, is 2,4-diacetamido-2,4,6-trideoxy-alpha-D-mannopyranose, which rapidly mutarotates to a mixture of anomers.The enzyme from Campylobacter jejuni, which incorporates legionaminicacid into flagellin, prefers GDP-N,N-diacetylbacillosamine.','UDP-N,N-diacetylbacillosamine + H(2)O = UDP + 2,4-diacetamido-2,4,6-trideoxy-D-mannopyranose.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.185','Non-reducing end beta-L-arabinofuranosidase','NULL','NULL','The enzyme, which was identified in the bacterium Bifidobacteriumlongum JCM1217, removes the beta-L-arabinofuranose residue from thenon-reducing end of multiple substrates, including beta-L-arabinofuranosyl-hydroxyproline (Ara-Hyp), Ara(2)-Hyp, Ara(3)-Hyp,and beta-L-arabinofuranosyl-(1-','Beta-L-arabinofuranosyl-(1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.186','Protodioscin 26-O-beta-D-glucosidase','Furostanol 26-O-beta-D-glucoside glucohydrolase','NULL','The enzyme has been characterized from the plants Cheilocostusspeciosus and Solanum torvum.It also hydrolyzes the 26-beta-D-glucose group from related steroidglucosides such as protogracillin, torvoside A and torvoside H.','Protodioscin + H(2)O = 26-deglucoprotodiscin + D-glucose.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.187','(Ara-f)(3)-Hyp beta-L-arabinobiosidase','Beta-L-arabinobiosidase','NULL','The enzyme, which was identified in the bacterium Bifidobacteriumlongum JCM1217, is specific for (Ara-f)(3)-Hyp, a sugar chain foundin hydroxyproline-rich glyoproteins such as extensin and lectin.The enzyme was not able to accept (Ara-f)(2)-Hyp or (Ara-f)(4)-Hyp assubstrates.In the presence of 1-alkanols, the enzyme demonstratestransglycosylation activity, retaining the anomeric configuration ofthe arabinofuranose residue.','4-O-(beta-L-arabinofuranosyl-(1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.188','Avenacosidase','NULL','NULL','Isolated from oat (Avena sativa) seedlings.The product acts as a defense system against fungal infection.Also acts on avenacoside A.','Avenacoside B + H(2)O = 26-desgluco-avenacoside B + D-glucose.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.189','Dioscin glycosidase (diosgenin-forming)','Dioscin glycosidase (aglycone-forming)','NULL','The enzyme is involved in degradation of the steroid saponin dioscinby some fungi of the Absidia genus.The enzyme can also hydrolyze 3-O-[alpha-L-Ara-(1-','3-O-[alpha-L-Rha-(1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.190','Dioscin glycosidase (3-O-beta-D-Glc-diosgenin-forming)','Dioscin-alpha-L-rhamnosidase','NULL','The enzyme is involved in the hydrolysis of the steroid saponindioscin by the digestive system of Sus scrofa (pig).Cf. EC 3.2.1.189.','3-O-[alpha-L-Rha-(1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.191','Ginsenosidase type III','NULL','NULL','Ginsenosidase type III catalyzes the sequential hydrolysis of the3-O-beta-D-(1-','A protopanaxadiol-type ginsenoside with two glucosyl residues at position3 + 2 H(2)O = a protopanaxadiol-type ginsenoside with no glycosidicmodification at position 3 + 2 D-glucopyranose.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.192','Ginsenoside Rb1 beta-glucosidase','NULL','NULL','Ginsenosidases catalyze the hydrolysis of glycosyl moieties attachedto the C-3, C-6 or C-20 position of ginsenosides.They are specific with respect to the nature of the glycosidiclinkage, the position and the order in which the linkages arecleaved.Ginsenoside Rb1 beta-glucosidase specifically and sequentiallyhydrolyzes the 20-(beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1-','Ginsenoside Rb1 + 2 H(2)O = ginsenoside Rg3 + 2 D-glucopyranose.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.193','Ginsenosidase type I','NULL','NULL','The enzyme hydrolyzes the 3-O-beta-D-(1-','(1) A protopanaxadiol-type ginsenoside with two glucosyl residues atposition 3 + H(2)O = a protopanaxadiol-type ginsenoside with one glucosylresidue at position 3 + D-glucopyranose.(2) A protopanaxadiol-type ginsenoside with one glucosyl residue atposition 3 + H(2)O = a protopanaxadiol-type ginsenoside with noglycosidic modifications at position 3 + D-glucopyranose.(3) A protopanaxadiol-type ginsenoside with two glycosyl residues atposition 20 + H(2)O = a protopanaxadiol-type ginsenoside with a singleglucosyl residue at position 20 + a monosaccharide.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.194','Ginsenosidase type IV','NULL','NULL','Ginsenosidase type IV catalyzes the sequential hydrolysis of the 6-O-beta-D-(1-','A protopanaxatriol-type ginsenoside with two glycosyl residues atposition 6 + 2 H(2)O = a protopanaxatriol-type ginsenoside with noglycosidic modification at position 6 + D-glucopyranose +a monosaccharide.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.195','20-O-multi-glycoside ginsenosidase','NULL','NULL','The 20-O-multi-glycoside ginsenosidase catalyzes the hydrolysis ofthe 20-O-alpha-(1-','A protopanaxadiol-type ginsenoside with two glycosyl residues at position20 + H(2)O = a protopanaxadiol-type ginsenoside with a single glucosylresidue at position 20 + a monosaccharide.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.n1','Blood group B branched chain alpha-1,3-galactosidase','NULL','NULL','The enzyme has exclusive specificity for the branched blood group Bstructures.','Hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing branched (1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.n2','Blood group B linear chain alpha-1,3-galactosidase','NULL','NULL','NULL','Hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing linear (1-', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.1.n3','Dictyostelium lysozyme A','NULL','NULL','Differs from EC 3.2.1.17, lysozyme, as it does not hydrolyze linkagesbetween N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues.','Hydrolysis of 1,4-beta-linkages between N-acetylmuramic acid andN-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues in a peptidoglycan.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.1','Purine nucleosidase','IAG-NH','NULL','The enzyme from the bacterium Ochrobactrum anthropi specificallycatalyzes the irreversible N-riboside hydrolysis of purinenucleosides.Pyrimidine nucleosides, purine and pyrimidine nucleotides, NAD(+),NADP(+) and nicotinaminde mononucleotide are not substrates.','A purine nucleoside + H(2)O = D-ribose + a purine base.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.2','Inosine nucleosidase','Inosinase','NULL','NULL','Inosine + H(2)O = D-ribose + hypoxanthine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.3','Uridine nucleosidase','Uridine ribohydrolase','NULL','NULL','Uridine + H(2)O = D-ribose + uracil.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.4','AMP nucleosidase','NULL','NULL','NULL','AMP + H(2)O = D-ribose 5-phosphate + adenine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.5','NAD(+) glycohydrolase','ADP-ribosyl cyclase','NULL','This enzyme catalyzes the hydrolysis of NAD(+), without associatedADP-ribosyl transferase or ADP-ribosyl cyclase activities (unlike themetazoan enzyme EC 3.2.2.6, bifunctional ADP-ribosyl cyclase/cyclicADP-ribose hydrolase).The enzyme from Group A streptococci has been implicated in thepathogenesis of diseases such as streptococcal toxic shock-likesyndrome (STSS) and necrotizing fasciitis.The enzyme from the venom of the snake Agkistrodon acutus alsocatalyzes EC 3.6.1.5.','NAD(+) + H(2)O = ADP-D-ribose + nicotinamide.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.6','ADP-ribosyl cyclase/cyclic ADP-ribose hydrolase','NAD hydrolase','NULL','This multiunctional enzyme catalyzes both the synthesis andhydrolysis of cyclic ADP-ribose, a calcium messenger that canmobilize intracellular Ca(2+) stores and activate Ca(2+) influx toregulate a wide range of physiological processes.In addition, the enzyme also catalyzes EC 2.4.99.20.Cf. EC 3.2.2.5.','NAD(+) + H(2)O = ADP-D-ribose + nicotinamide.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.7','Adenosine nucleosidase','Adenosinase','NULL','Also acts on adenosine N-oxide.','Adenosine + H(2)O = D-ribose + adenine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.8','Ribosylpyrimidine nucleosidase','N-ribosylpyrimidine nucleosidase','NULL','Also hydrolyzes purine D-ribonucleosides, more slowly.2-, 3- and 5-deoxynucleosides are not substrates.','A pyrimidine nucleoside + H(2)O = D-ribose + a pyrimidine base.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.9','Adenosylhomocysteine nucleosidase','5-methyladenosine nucleosidase','NULL','NULL','(1) S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + H(2)O = S-(5-deoxy-D-ribos-5-yl)-L-homocysteine + adenine.(2) S-methyl-5-thioadenosine + H(2)O = 5-methyl-5-thio-D-ribose +adenine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.10','Pyrimidine-5-nucleotide nucleosidase','Pyr5N','NULL','Also acts on dUMP, dTMP and dCMP.','A pyrimidine 5-nucleotide + H(2)O = D-ribose 5-phosphate + a pyrimidinebase.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.11','Beta-aspartyl-N-acetylglucosaminidase','NULL','NULL','NULL','1-beta-aspartyl-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminylamine + H(2)O = L-asparagine +N-acetyl-D-glucosamine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.12','Inosinate nucleosidase','NULL','NULL','NULL','5-inosinate + H(2)O = D-ribose 5-phosphate + hypoxanthine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.13','1-methyladenosine nucleosidase','NULL','NULL','NULL','1-methyladenosine + H(2)O = 1-methyladenine + D-ribose.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.14','NMN nucleosidase','NMNase','NULL','NULL','Beta-nicotinamide D-ribonucleotide + H(2)O = D-ribose 5-phosphate +nicotinamide.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.15','DNA-deoxyinosine glycosylase','DNA(hypoxanthine) glycohydrolase','NULL','NULL','Hydrolyzes DNA and polynucleotides, releasing free hypoxanthine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.16','Methylthioadenosine nucleosidase','5-methylthioadenosine nucleosidase','NULL','Does not act on S-adenosylhomocysteine (cf. EC 3.2.2.9).','S-methyl-5-thioadenosine + H(2)O = S-methyl-5-thio-D-ribose + adenine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.17','Deoxyribodipyrimidine endonucleosidase','Pyrimidine dimer DNA-glycosylase','NULL','NULL','Cleaves the N-glycosidic bond between the 5-pyrimidine residue incyclobutadipyrimidine (in DNA) and the corresponding deoxy-D-riboseresidue.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.18','Transferred entry: 3','NULL','NULL','NULL','NULL', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.19','[Protein ADP-ribosylarginine] hydrolase','ADP-ribose-L-arginine cleavage enzyme','NULL','The enzyme will remove ADP-D-ribose from arginine residues in ADP-ribosylated proteins.','(1) Protein-N(omega)-(ADP-D-ribosyl)-L-arginine + H(2)O = ADP-D-ribose +protein-L-arginine.(2) N(omega)-(ADP-D-ribosyl)-L-arginine + H(2)O = ADP-D-ribose +L-arginine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.20','DNA-3-methyladenine glycosylase I','DNA glycosidase I','NULL','NULL','Hydrolysis of alkylated DNA, releasing 3-methyladenine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.21','DNA-3-methyladenine glycosylase II','DNA glycosidase II','NULL','NULL','Hydrolysis of alkylated DNA, releasing 3-methyladenine, 3-methylguanine,7-methylguanine and 7-methyladenine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.22','rRNA N-glycosylase','rRNA N-glycosidase','NULL','Ricin A-chain and related toxins show this activity.Naked rRNA is attacked more slowly than rRNA in intact ribosomes.Naked rRNA from Escherichia coli is cleaved at a correspondingposition.','Endohydrolysis of the N-glycosidic bond at one specific adenosine on the28S rRNA.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.23','DNA-formamidopyrimidine glycosylase','Fapy-DNA glycosylase','NULL','May play a significant role in processes leading to recovery frommutagenesis and/or cell death by alkylating agents.Also involved in the GO system responsible for removing anoxidatively damaged form of guanine (7,8-dihydro-8-oxoguanine) fromDNA.','Hydrolysis of DNA containing ring-opened 7-methylguanine residues,releasing 2,6-diamino-4-hydroxy-5-(N-methyl)formamidopyrimidine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.24','ADP-ribosyl-[dinitrogen reductase] hydrolase','ADP-ribosyl glycohydrolase','NULL','Together with EC 2.4.2.37, controls the level of activity ofEC 1.18.6.1.','ADP-D-ribosyl-[dinitrogen reductase] = ADP-D-ribose + [dinitrogenreductase].', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.25','N-methyl nucleosidase','7-methylxanthosine nucleosidase','NULL','Preferentially hydrolyzes 3- and 7-methylpurine nucleosides, such as3-methylxanthosine, 3-methyladenosine and 7-methylguanosine.Hydrolysis of 7-methylxanthosine to form 7-methylxanthine is thesecond step in the caffeine biosynthesis pathway.','7-methylxanthosine + H(2)O = 7-methylxanthine + D-ribose.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.26','Futalosine hydrolase','Futalosine nucleosidase','NULL','This enzyme, which is specific for futalosine, catalyzes the secondstep of a novel menaquinone biosynthetic pathway that is found insome prokaryotes.','Futalosine + H(2)O = dehypoxanthine futalosine + hypoxanthine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.27','Uracil-DNA glycosylase','Uracil DNA glycohydrolase','NULL','Uracil-DNA glycosylases are widespread enzymes that are found in allliving organisms.Uracil-DNA glycosylase (EC 3.2.2.27) and double-stranded uracil-DNAglycosylase (EC 3.2.2.28) form a central part of the DNA-repairmachinery since they initiate the DNA base-excision repair pathway byhydrolyzing the N-glycosidic bond between uracil and the deoxyribosesugar thereby catalyzing the removal of mis-incorporated uracil fromDNA.','Hydrolyzes single-stranded DNA or mismatched double-stranded DNA andpolynucleotides, releasing free uracil.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.28','Double-stranded uracil-DNA glycosylase','DsUDG','NULL','No activity on DNA containing a T/G mispair or single-stranded DNAcontaining either a site-specific uracil or 3,N(4)-ethenocytosineresidue, significant role for double-stranded uracil-DNA glycosylasein mutation avoidance in non-dividing Escherichia coli.Uracil-DNA glycosylases are widespread enzymes that are found in allliving organisms.Uracil-DNA glycosylase (EC 3.2.2.27) and double-stranded uracil-DNAglycosylase (EC 3.2.2.28) form a central part of the DNA-repairmachinery since they initiate the DNA base-excision repair pathway byhydrolyzing the N-glycosidic bond between uracil and the deoxyribosesugar thereby catalyzing the removal of mis-incorporated uracil fromDNA.','Specifically hydrolyzes mismatched double-stranded DNA andpolynucleotides, releasing free uracil.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.2.29','Thymine-DNA glycosylase','Mismatch-specific thymine-DNA glycosylase','NULL','Thymine-DNA glycosylase is part of the DNA-repair machinery.Thymine removal is fastest when it is from a G/T mismatch with a5-flanking C/G pair.The glycosylase removes uracil from G/U, C/U, and T/U base pairsfaster than it removes thymine from G/T.','Hydrolyzes mismatched double-stranded DNA and polynucleotides, releasingfree thymine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.2.3.1','Transferred entry: 3','NULL','NULL','NULL','NULL', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.1.1','Adenosylhomocysteinase','Adenosylhomocysteine hydrolase','NAD(+).','The NAD(+) cofactor appears to bring about a transient oxidation atC-3 of the 5-deoxyadenosine residue, thus labilizing the thioetherbond cf. EC 5.5.1.4.','S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + H(2)O = L-homocysteine + adenosine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.1.2','Adenosylmethionine hydrolase','Methylmethionine-sulfonium-salt hydrolase','NULL','Also hydrolyzes methylmethionine sulfonium salt to dimethyl sulfideand homoserine.','S-adenosyl-L-methionine + H(2)O = L-homoserine + methylthioadenosine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.1.3','Transferred entry: 4','NULL','NULL','NULL','NULL', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.2.1','Isochorismatase','2,3-dihydro-2,3-dihydroxybenzoate synthase','NULL','NULL','Isochorismate + H(2)O = (2S,3S)-2,3-dihydroxy-2,3-dihydrobenzoate +pyruvate.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.2.2','Alkenylglycerophosphocholine hydrolase','NULL','NULL','NULL','1-(1-alkenyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine + H(2)O = an aldehyde +sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.2.3','Transferred entry: 3','NULL','NULL','NULL','NULL', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.2.4','Trans-epoxysuccinate hydrolase','Trans-epoxysuccinate hydratase','NULL','Acts on both optical isomers of the substrate.Formerly EC 4.2.1.37.','Trans-2,3-epoxysuccinate + H(2)O = meso-tartrate.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.2.5','Alkenylglycerophosphoethanolamine hydrolase','NULL','NULL','NULL','1-(1-alkenyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine + H(2)O = an aldehyde +sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.2.6','Leukotriene-A(4) hydrolase','Leukotriene A(4) hydrolase','Zinc.','A bifunctional zinc metalloprotease that displays both epoxidehydrolase and aminopeptidase activities.It preferentially cleaves tripeptides at an arginyl bond, withdipeptides and tetrapeptides being poorer substrates.It also converts leukotriene A(4) into leukotriene B(4), unlikeEC 3.2.2.10 which converts leukotriene A(4) into 5,6-dihydroxy-7,9,11,14-eicosatetraenoic acid.','(7E,9E,11Z,14Z)-(5S,6S)-5,6-epoxyicosa-7,9,11,14-tetraenoate + H(2)O =(6Z,8E,10E,14Z)-(5S,12R)-5,12-dihydroxyicosa-6,8,10,14-tetraenoate.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.2.7','Hepoxilin-epoxide hydrolase','Hepoxilin A(3) hydrolase','NULL','Converts hepoxilin A(3) into trioxilin A(3).Highly specific for the substrate, having only slight activity withother epoxides such as leukotriene A(4) and styrene oxide.Probably plays a modulatory role in inflammation, vascularphysiology, systemic glucose metabolism and neurological function.','(5Z,9E,14Z)-(8-xi,11R,12S)-11,12-epoxy-8-hydroxyicosa-5,9,14-trienoate +H(2)O = (5Z,9E,14Z)-(8-xi,11-xi,12S)-8,11,12-trihydroxyicosa-5,9,14-trienoate.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.2.8','Limonene-1,2-epoxide hydrolase','Limonene oxide hydrolase','NULL','Involved in the monoterpene degradation pathway of the actinomyceteRhodococcus erythropolis.The enzyme hydrolyzes several alicyclic and 1-methyl-substitutedepoxides, such as 1-methylcyclohexene oxide, indene oxide andcyclohexene oxide.It differs from the previously described epoxide hydrolases(EC 3.3.2.4, EC 3.3.2.6, EC 3.3.2.7, EC 3.3.2.9 and EC 3.3.2.10) asit is not inhibited by 2-bromo-4-nitroacetophenone, diethylpyrocarbonate, 4-fluorochalcone oxide or 1,10-phenanthroline.','1,2-epoxymenth-8-ene + H(2)O = menth-8-ene-1,2-diol.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.2.9','Microsomal epoxide hydrolase','Arene-oxide hydratase','NULL','Involved in the metabolism of numerous xenobiotics, such as 1,3-butadiene oxide, styrene oxide and the polycyclic aromatichydrocarbon benzo[a]pyrene 4,5-oxide.In a series of oxiranes with a lipophilic substituent of sufficientsize (styrene oxides), monosubstituted as well as 1,1- and cis-1,2-disubstituted oxiranes serve as substrates or inhibitors of theenzyme, while trans-1,2-disubstituted, tri- and tetra-substitutedoxiranes are not substrates.The reaction involves the formation of an hydroxyalkyl-enzymeintermediate.Formerly EC 3.3.2.3, EC 4.2.1.63 and EC 4.2.1.64.','Cis-stilbene oxide + H(2)O = (+)-(1R,2R)-1,2-diphenylethane-1,2-diol.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.2.10','Soluble epoxide hydrolase','Arene-oxide hydratase','NULL','Catalyzes the hydrolysis of trans-substituted epoxides, such astrans-stilbene oxide, as well as various aliphatic epoxides derivedfrom fatty-acid metabolism.It is involved in the metabolism of arachidonic epoxides(epoxyeicosatrienoic acids; EETs) and linoleic acid epoxides.The enzyme from mammals is a bifunctional enzyme: the C-terminaldomain exhibits epoxide-hydrolase activity and the N-terminal domainhas the activity of EC 3.1.3.76.Like EC 3.3.2.9, it is probable that the reaction involves theformation of an hydroxyalkyl-enzyme intermediate.The enzyme can also use leukotriene A(4), the substrate ofEC 3.3.2.6, but it forms 5,6-dihydroxy-7,9,11,14-eicosatetraenoicacid rather than leukotriene B(4) as the product.Formerly EC 3.3.2.3, EC 4.2.1.63 and EC 4.2.1.64.','An epoxide + H(2)O = a glycol.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.2.11','Cholesterol-5,6-oxide hydrolase','ChEH','NULL','The enzyme appears to work equally well with both diastereoisomers ofcholesterol 5,6-epoxide.The product is a competitive inhibitor of the reaction.','(1) 5,6-alpha-epoxy-5-alpha-cholestan-3-beta-ol + H(2)O = cholestane-3-beta,5-alpha,6-beta-triol.(2) 5,6-beta-epoxy-5-beta-cholestan-3-beta-ol + H(2)O = cholestane-3-beta,5-alpha,6-beta-triol.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.2.12','Oxepin-CoA hydrolase','NULL','NULL','The enzyme from Escherichia coli is a bifunctional fusion proteinthat also catalyzes EC 1.17.1.7.Combined the two activities result in a two-step conversion ofoxepin-CoA to 3-oxo-5,6-dehydrosuberyl-CoA, part of an aerobicphenylacetate degradation pathway.The enzyme from Escherichia coli also exhibits enoyl-CoA hydrataseactivity utilizing crotonyl-CoA as a substrate.Formerly EC 3.7.1.16.','2-oxepin-2(3H)-ylideneacetyl-CoA + H(2)O = 3-oxo-5,6-dehydrosuberyl-CoAsemialdehyde.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.2.13','Chorismatase','Chorismate/3,4-dihydroxycyclohexa-1,5-dienoate synthase','NULL','The enzyme found in several bacterial species is involved in thebiosynthesis of macrocyclic polyketides.','Chorismate + H(2)O = (3R,4R)-3,4-dihydroxy-3,4-dihydrobenzoate +pyruvate.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
INSERT INTO enzyme VALUES ( 'EC 3.3.2.30','Aminodeoxyfutalosine nucleosidase','AFL nucleosidase','NULL','The enzyme, found in several bacterial species, also has the activityof EC 3.2.2.9.It is part of a modified futalosine pathway for menaquinonebiosynthesis.','6-amino-6-deoxyfutalosine + H(2)O = dehypoxanthine futalosine + adenine.', 'NULL', 'NULL');
